poor show
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:usual NZ equivalent of <i>bad show</i> (cf P.) and <i>put up a show</i> (cf P. orig. mily: 1915). Used occas. to express disapproval, but mainly in the sense of `a poor showing, display; state of affairs; behaviour'. Almost now a c.p. [? omit]
Origin:[none]
